ThousandSteps Privacy Policy


The ThousandSteps app respects and protects the privacy of all users who use the service. In order to provide you with more accurate and personalized services, the Custom App will use and disclose your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
However, the ThousandSteps App will treat this information with a high degree of diligence and prudence. Except as otherwise provided in this Privacy Policy, this information will not be disclosed or made available to third parties without your prior permission. The ThousandSteps App will update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
By agreeing to the ThousandSteps Service Use Agreement, you are deemed to have agreed to the entire content of this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy is an integral part of the ThousandSteps Service Use Agreement.

1. Scope of application

a) When you register for a ThousandSteps App account, you will be provided with the personal registration information required by the ThousandSteps App;

b) When you use the ThousandSteps App network service, or access the ThousandSteps platform webpage, you are accustomed to the information on your browser and computer that the App automatically receives and records, including but not limited to your IP address, browser type Data, language used, date and time of access, hardware and software feature information, and web page records you need;

c)ThousandSteps to the user's personal data obtained by the App from the business partners through legal channels.

You understand and agree that the following information does not apply to this Privacy Policy:

a) Keyword information that you enter when using the search service provided by the ThousandSteps app platform;

b) ThousandSteps get used to the relevant information data that you have collected in the ThousandSteps app, including but not limited to participation activities, transaction information and evaluation details;

c) Violation of the law or violation of the customary App rules and ThousandSteps of the measures that the App has taken against you.

2. Information use

a) ThousandSteps App does not offer, sell, rent, share or trade your personal information to any unrelated third party unless you have your permission in advance, or the third party and the lightly used App (including ThousandSteps App affiliates) are separate Or jointly provide services to you, and after the service is over, it will be banned from accessing all such materials that it has previously been able to access.

b) The ThousandSteps App does not allow any third party to collect, edit, sell or distribute your personal information by any means. Any user who is accustomed to the App platform, if engaged in the above activities, once discovered, the Apprentice App has the right to immediately terminate the service agreement with the user.

c) For the purpose of serving the user, the App may use the personal information to provide you with information that you are interested in, including but not limited to, sending you product and service information, or sharing information with a ThousandSteps App partner. They send you information about their products and services (the latter requires your prior consent).

3. Information disclosure

Under the following circumstances, the ThousandSteps App will disclose your personal information in whole or in part according to your personal wishes or the law:

a) disclose to third parties with your prior consent;

b) in order to provide the products and services you request, you must share your personal information with third parties;

c) disclosure to third parties or administrative or judicial authorities in accordance with the relevant provisions of the law, or at the request of the administrative or judicial authorities;

d) If you are in violation of relevant Chinese laws, regulations or ThousandSteps App service agreements or related rules, you need to disclose to third parties;

e) If you are a qualified IP Complainant and have filed a complaint, it should be disclosed to the Respondent at the request of the Complainant so that both parties can handle possible rights disputes;

f) In a transaction created on the ThousandSteps App platform, if any party to the transaction performs or partially fulfills the transaction obligation and makes a request for information disclosure, the ThousandSteps App has the right to decide to provide the user with the contact information of the counterparty, etc. The necessary information to facilitate the completion of the transaction or the resolution of the dispute.

g) Other ThousandSteps App disclosures deemed appropriate by law, regulation or website policy.

4. Information storage and exchange

The information and materials collected by the App used by the App will be stored on the server of the Custom App and/or its affiliates. The information and materials may be sent to your country, region or the location where the App collects information and materials. It is accessed, stored and displayed outside the country and abroad.

5. Use of cookies

a) If you have not refused to accept cookies, the Custom App will set or access cookies on your computer so that you can log in or use the ThousandSteps App platform services or features that rely on cookies. ThousandSteps app use cookies to provide you with more thoughtful and personalized services, including promotional services.

b) You have the right to choose to accept or decline to accept cookies. You can refuse to accept cookies by modifying your browser settings. However, if you choose to refuse to accept cookies, you may not be able to log in or use a ThousandSteps App web service or feature that relies on cookies.

c) This policy will apply to information obtained through the use of cookies set by the App.

6. Information security

a) ThousandSteps App accounts have security protection functions, please keep your username and password information safe. The ThousandSteps App will ensure that your information is not lost, misused and altered by security measures such as encrypting the user's password. Despite the aforementioned security measures, please also note that there are no “perfect security measures” on the information network.

b) When using the ThousandSteps App network service for online transactions, you will inevitably disclose your personal information, such as contact information or postal address, to the counterparty or potential counterparty
